{
  "video_id": "gQbZX9JEQsQ",
  "title": "Did ancient Troy really exist? - Einav Zamir Dembin",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 8612.0,
      "end_time": 12876.0,
      "text": "When Homer's Iliad was first written down in the 8th century BCE,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 12876.0,
      "end_time": 16192.0,
      "text": "the story of the Trojan war was already an old one."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 16192.0,
      "end_time": 17799.0,
      "text": "From existing oral tradition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 17799.0,
      "end_time": 20718.0,
      "text": "audiences knew the tales of the long siege,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 20718.0,
      "end_time": 23427.0,
      "text": "the epic duels outside the city walls,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 23427.0,
      "end_time": 26156.0,
      "text": "and the cunning trick that finally won the war."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 26156.0,
      "end_time": 29671.0,
      "text": "In the end, the magnificent city was burned to the ground,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 29672.0,
      "end_time": 31509.0,
      "text": "never to rise again."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 31509.0,
      "end_time": 34100.0,
      "text": "But had it ever existed?"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 34100.0,
      "end_time": 39153.0,
      "text": "By the time the field of archaeology began to take shape in the 19th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 39153.0,
      "end_time": 43272.0,
      "text": "many were skeptical, considering the epic to be pure fiction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 43273.0,
      "end_time": 47840.0,
      "text": "a founding myth imagining a bygone heroic era."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 47840.0,
      "end_time": 48413.0,
      "text": "But some scholars believed"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 48413.0,
      "end_time": 51887.0,
      "text": "that behind the superhuman feats and divine miracles"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 51887.0,
      "end_time": 54754.0,
      "text": "there must have been a grain of historical truth -"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 54754.0,
      "end_time": 56437.0,
      "text": "a war that was really fought,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 56437.0,
      "end_time": 58638.0,
      "text": "and a place where it happened."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 58638.0,
      "end_time": 61187.0,
      "text": "Frank Calvert was one such believer."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 61187.0,
      "end_time": 65120.0,
      "text": "He had spent his youth traveling and learning about ancient civilizations"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 65120.00000000001,
      "end_time": 67860.0,
      "text": "before accompanying his brother Frederick"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 67860.0,
      "end_time": 71970.0,
      "text": "on a diplomatic mission to the northwest Anatolian region of Çanakkale."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 71970.0,
      "end_time": 74993.0,
      "text": "It was here that Homer described the Greek encampment"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 74993.0,
      "end_time": 77411.0,
      "text": "at the mouth of the Scamander river."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 77411.0,
      "end_time": 80519.0,
      "text": "And it was here that fate brought Frank into contact"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 80519.0,
      "end_time": 84261.0,
      "text": "with a journalist and geologist named Charles Maclaren."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 84261.0,
      "end_time": 86289.0,
      "text": "Locals and travelers had long speculated"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 86289.0,
      "end_time": 89862.0,
      "text": "that Troy might've stood on one of the surrounding hilltops."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 89862.0,
      "end_time": 92200.0,
      "text": "But Maclaren had been one of the first"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 92200.0,
      "end_time": 95694.0,
      "text": "to publish a detailed topographical study of the area."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 95694.0,
      "end_time": 97651.0,
      "text": "He believed he had found the site –"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 97651.0,
      "end_time": 101500.0,
      "text": "a 32-meter mound known by the name Hisarlık,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 101500.0,
      "end_time": 103806.0,
      "text": "derived from the Turkish word  for \"fortress.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 103806.0,
      "end_time": 106224.0,
      "text": "Soon after meeting with him in 1847,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 106224.0,
      "end_time": 108708.0,
      "text": "the Calverts bought 2,000 acres of farmland"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 108708.0,
      "end_time": 111620.0,
      "text": "that included part of the hill."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 111620.0,
      "end_time": 113600.0,
      "text": "Before they could explore any further,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 113600.0,
      "end_time": 114949.0,
      "text": "the Crimean War broke out"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 114949.0,
      "end_time": 118712.0,
      "text": "and forestalled their archaeological ambitions for several years."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 118712.0,
      "end_time": 120382.0,
      "text": "After the war's end,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 120382.0,
      "end_time": 122554.0,
      "text": "Frank Calvert began to survey the site,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 122554.0,
      "end_time": 125628.0,
      "text": "but lacked the funds for a full excavation."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 125628.0,
      "end_time": 127984.0,
      "text": "This was where the wealthy German businessman"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 127984.0,
      "end_time": 132300.0,
      "text": "and amateur archaeologist Heinrich Schliemann came in."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 132300.0,
      "end_time": 133576.0,
      "text": "At Calvert's invitation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 133576.0,
      "end_time": 138438.0,
      "text": "Schliemann visited the grounds in 1868, and decided to excavate."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 138438.0,
      "end_time": 140194.0,
      "text": "Eager to find the ancient city,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 140194.0,
      "end_time": 144116.0,
      "text": "Schliemann tore massive trenches all the way to the base of the hill."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 144116.0,
      "end_time": 147871.0,
      "text": "There, he uncovered a hoard of precious artifacts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 147871.0,
      "end_time": 148603.0,
      "text": "jewelry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 148603.0,
      "end_time": 149414.0,
      "text": "and metalwork,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 149414.0,
      "end_time": 152399.0,
      "text": "including two diadems and a copper shield."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 152400.0,
      "end_time": 154799.0,
      "text": "Schliemann took full credit for the discovery,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 154799.0,
      "end_time": 156698.0,
      "text": "announcing that he had found Troy"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 156698.0,
      "end_time": 158949.0,
      "text": "and the treasure of its king Priam."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 158949.0,
      "end_time": 160950.0,
      "text": "But the real treasure was elsewhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 160950.0,
      "end_time": 163277.0,
      "text": "When later archaeologists studied the site,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 163277.0,
      "end_time": 167704.0,
      "text": "they realized that the mound consisted of no less than nine cities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 167705.0,
      "end_time": 170399.0,
      "text": "each built atop the ruins of the last."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 170399.0,
      "end_time": 174166.0,
      "text": "The layer Schliemann had uncovered dated back to the Mycenaean Age,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 174166.0,
      "end_time": 177323.0,
      "text": "more than 1,000 years too early for Homer."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 177324.0,
      "end_time": 179813.0,
      "text": "But inside the mound was indeed evidence"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 179813.0,
      "end_time": 182809.0,
      "text": "for a city that had thrived during the Bronze Age,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 182809.0,
      "end_time": 183994.0,
      "text": "with charred stone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 183994.0,
      "end_time": 185575.0,
      "text": "broken arrowheads,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 185575.0,
      "end_time": 189432.0,
      "text": "and damaged human skeletons suggesting a violent end."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 189432.0,
      "end_time": 192380.0,
      "text": "It was Troy VII, contained in the middle layers"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 192380.0,
      "end_time": 197176.0,
      "text": "and now ravaged for a second time by Schliemann's careless excavation."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 197176.0,
      "end_time": 200814.0,
      "text": "The settlement, spanning some 200,000 square meters"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 200814.0,
      "end_time": 203333.0,
      "text": "and home to as many as 10,000 people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 203333.0,
      "end_time": 206590.0,
      "text": "thrived until around 1180 BCE."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 206590.0,
      "end_time": 209682.0,
      "text": "Its position at the southern entrance of the Dardanelles strait"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 209682.0,
      "end_time": 214950.0,
      "text": "would've made a formidable strategic location for both defense and trade."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 214950.0,
      "end_time": 218362.0,
      "text": "Most importantly, there are the remains of a massive fortification wall –"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 218362.0,
      "end_time": 220780.0,
      "text": "perhaps the very same one"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 220780.0,
      "end_time": 224306.0,
      "text": "from which Priam and Hector once watched the Greeks approach."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 224306.0,
      "end_time": 226412.0,
      "text": "Of course, it's difficult to be certain"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 226412.0,
      "end_time": 230314.0,
      "text": "that these ruins are the true remains of ancient Troy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 230314.0,
      "end_time": 231771.0,
      "text": "and scholars still dispute"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 231771.0,
      "end_time": 235432.0,
      "text": "whether the Trojan War as described by Homer ever happened."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 235432.0,
      "end_time": 237214.0,
      "text": "Yet the evidence is strong enough"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 237214.0,
      "end_time": 241615.0,
      "text": "that UNESCO has labelled Hisarlık the archeological site of Troy."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 241615.0,
      "end_time": 243270.0,
      "text": "Regardless of its identity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 243270.0,
      "end_time": 244679.0,
      "text": "thanks to persistence,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 244680.0,
      "end_time": 245755.0,
      "text": "a bit of faith,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 245755.0,
      "end_time": 247162.0,
      "text": "and a lot of research,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 247162.0,
      "end_time": 250229.0,
      "text": "archaeologists are bringing the long-buried secrets"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 250229.0,
      "end_time": 252909.0,
      "text": "of an ancient, lost city to light."
    }
  ]
}